                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="425737" author="pjones" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2024 22:08:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged for 2.16&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="425672" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2024 21:55:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54666/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54666/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14853&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity: create ldiskfs and zfs filesystem upgrade images for 2.15&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14853&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14853&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: conf-sanity/32 upgrade 2.14/2.15 images&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 74a5b9efaaecfb1f910c60ae66deb6f113dc5b00&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="423303" author="yujian" created="Fri, 2 Aug 2024 23:41:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch passed autotesting with ldiskfs and zfs.&lt;br/&gt;
Lustre Gerrit Janitor zfs test sessions failed with ATM-3235.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="422003" author="yujian" created="Tue, 23 Jul 2024 14:34:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The configuration and checks for file data encryption and filename encryption were added to the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="421298" author="yujian" created="Wed, 17 Jul 2024 15:43:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I updated patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/54666&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/54666&lt;/a&gt; to add checks for OST pools and OST Pool Quotas. Proceed with adding checks for fscrypt data encryption and filename encryption.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="409954" author="adilger" created="Wed, 3 Apr 2024 22:55:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed a starter patch to get the ball rolling on this, but it will need input from a few others to finish the work:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=scherementsev&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;scherementsev&quot;&gt;scherementsev&lt;/a&gt; (or someone else) to add configuration and later checks for OST pools and OST pool quotas&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sebastien&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sebastien&quot;&gt;sebastien&lt;/a&gt; (or someone else) to add configuration and later checks for file data encryption (in 2.14.0) and filename encryption (in 2.15.0)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Deiter&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Deiter&quot;&gt;Deiter&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sarah&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sarah&quot;&gt;sarah&lt;/a&gt; to work with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=colmstea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;colmstea&quot;&gt;colmstea&lt;/a&gt; to split the conf-sanity test_32 tests into a separate test session (per &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14772&quot; title=&quot;split conf-sanity into 2 or 3 parts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14772&quot;&gt;LU-14772&lt;/a&gt;), since conf-sanity is by far the longest-running test script (8.5-11.5h) and adding more tests and images will only make it take longer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I think we are exposing ourselves to hard-to-fix bugs and interop issues if we make a new release without having any tests that are verifying the on-disk format is not broken when new patches are landed.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="409953" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 3 Apr 2024 22:38:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54666&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54666&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14853&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity: create ldiskfs and zfs filesystem upgrade images for 2.15&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14853&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14853&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: conf-sanity/32 upgrade 2.14/2.15 images&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 9c913a0a1dc69edcc35f843ac82d7ee010026c4f&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="332281" author="adilger" created="Mon, 18 Apr 2022 20:49:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please also fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10215&quot; title=&quot;disk2_5-ldiskfs.tar.bz2 is not packaged into test rpm&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10215&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10215&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (add ldiskfs 2.5 image to RPM) at the same time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="324640" author="adilger" created="Mon, 31 Jan 2022 21:04:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test images themselves should be created as sparse files, to reduce the amount of space used.  It &lt;em&gt;might&lt;/em&gt; be possible to run &quot;&lt;tt&gt;fstrim&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; on the mounted filesystems to have the kernel punch out holes in the files, but maybe only with newer kernels.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
